{{Synthesis | reason=No apparent reason relationships in this list are exclusively "special"; smacks of original research; ideally need a source that provides a strict definition and a specific list that meets those criteria|date=October 2018}}
{{For|other uses|Special Relationship (disambiguation)}}
A '''special relationship''' is a diplomatic relationship that is especially strong and important. This term is usually used to refer to the [[Special Relationship|historic relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom]]. In its extended use outside it and the [[Anglosphere]], it has also been used to describe the whole of [[United States – European Union relations|EU–US relations]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eeas.europa.eu/top_stories/2011/251111_eu_us_relations_en.htm|title=European Union - EEAS (European External Action Service) - The EU and the US: a special relationship|publisher=}}</ref> and the following relations:
